            "description": "Heat 1 tablespoon of sunflower oil in a medium frying pan over medium-high heat. Spoon about 3 tablespoons of the mixture into the center of the pan and flatten it with the underside of the spoon to form fritters that are 2-3cm thick. Fry each fritter for 2-3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Repeat this process with the remaining batter to make about 8 fritters."
